2.title: Childhood

episode of.title: The Traveler's Guide to Life (TV Series 2011– )

2.plot: Join host Adam Richman and guests Andre Ethier, Bert Kreischer, Aaron Fotheringham, Natasha Leggero, Suzanne Rauscher, Phil Rosenthal, David Weisenberg, Shereen Mirtavoosi, Matt Sims and John Salley as they share the childhood adventures that started their journey on the highway of life.

3.title: Hometown

episode of.title: The Traveler's Guide to Life (TV Series 2011– )

3.plot: In this episode of The Traveler's Guide To Life, host Adam Richman and guests, including Roma Maffia, Cat Cora, Romy Rosemont, John Salley, Evan Lysacek, CCH Pounder, Louie Vito, Chris Gore, Natalie Miller and Chris Thile, let us in on the unique traditions, awesome food and significant experiences that still draw them back to the places where their journeys began.

4.title: Work

episode of.title: The Traveler's Guide to Life (TV Series 2011– )

4.plot: Join host Adam Richman and guests Joe Wengert, Aaron Conte, Shereen Mirtavoosi, Suzanne Rauscher, Rachel Hollis, Phil Rosenthal, Jimmy Pardo, Constance Marie, Steven Ho and Story Musgrave as they share stories about transcending the daily grind. They'll reveal moments that remind us that work can be worthwhile.

5.title: Love

episode of.title: The Traveler's Guide to Life (TV Series 2011– )

5.plot: In this episode of The Traveler's Guide to Life, join host Adam Richman and several guests Andrew Zimmern, Aaron Conte, Bert Kreischer, Constance Marie, Darlene Kegan, Miriyam Glazer, Anthony Elman, Natasha Leggero, Rochelle Vallese, Natalie Miller and Jodi Miller, as they share stories of love lost and found. From innocent stories of the first kiss to finding the love of your life at a ripe old age, love can turn your world upside down, set your heart on fire and still have a happy ending.

6.title: Celebrations

episode of.title: The Traveler's Guide to Life (TV Series 2011– )

6.plot: Join host Adam Richman and several other revelers, including Constance Marie, Shereen Mirtavoosi, Eric Greenspan, Charlyne Yi, Michael Parks, John Salley, Andrew Zimmern, Kelly Kovacic and Chris Thile, as they share stories of holidays, rituals and events that changed their lives. Whether things went surprisingly well or disastrously awry, these festivities were turning points for each storyteller and their lives were never the same again.

7.title: Family

episode of.title: The Traveler's Guide to Life (TV Series 2011– )

7.plot: In this episode of The Traveler's Guide To Life, host Adam Richman and several guests, including Doug Jones, Alexandra Paul, Rachel Hollis, Shereen Mirtavoosi, Rachael Leigh Cook, Bert Kreischer, Andrew Zimmern, Greg Louganis, Steven Ho and Joe Zee, explore the ties that bind. From non-traditional family celebrations to that moment when we finally gain approval from a loved one, these are stories that get to the core of who we are and where we came from.

8.title: Winning

episode of.title: The Traveler's Guide to Life (TV Series 2011– )

8.plot: Join fellow champions as they share their most inspiring victorious moments and the secrets to their success. Eric Greenspan, Peter Wallerstein, Aaron Fotheringham, Andre Ethier, Doug Jones, Maurice James, Trey Sorensen, Evan Lysacek, Charlyne Yi and Alexandra Paul tell their stories about beating the odds and accomplishing their goals.

9.title: Friendship

episode of.title: The Traveler's Guide to Life (TV Series 2011– )

9.plot: Join host Adam Richman and several guests, including John Salley, Rob Stewart, Joe Zee, Carl Reiner, Mike Henry, Kelly Kovacic, Jodi Miller, Joe Wengert, Katrina Drabkin and Phil Rosenthal, as they discuss the people who shaped their lives and the moments they shared with them. Whether it's someone you grew up with or someone with whom you discovered an unlikely bond, friendships makes life's journey much more fun.

10.title: Secret Lives

episode of.title: The Traveler's Guide to Life (TV Series 2011– )

10.plot: Join host Adam Richman and several guests, including Antonio Sabato Jr, Eric Greenspan, Rob Stewart, Romy Rosemont, Rachelle Murphy, David Weisenberg, Greg Louganis, Louie Vito and Doug Jones, as they let us in on secrets big and small. Some of our guests have hidden talents and secret collections. One even went undercover to date an icon. Who knew a secret life could be so much fun?
